Minor point:
I realise this is a common pattern within the BackDoor. I am personally not a fan of sweeping through a list to find and return an item inside. The happy path is not very clear either :P
This is an alternate way of doing it:
FeedbackSessionData feedbackSession =  
    sessionsData.getFeedbackSessions()
                .stream()
                .filter(fs -> fs.getFeedbackSessionName().equals(feedbackSessionName))
                .findFirst()
                .orElse(null);

if (feedbackSession == null) {
    return null;
}

return FeedbackSessionAttributes
        .builder(feedbackSession.getCourseId(), 
                 feedbackSession.getFeedbackSessionName())
        .build();

